VNET (Virtual Network)  subnet , route table, gateway
- Private network in Azure.
- Enables communication between Azure resources.
- Similar to a network in a data center.
- Supports subnets, NSGs, route tables.
- Provides network isolation and security.

Subnet
- Logical division of a VNET.
- Helps organize resources by function.
- Each subnet has its own IP range.
- NSGs can be applied at subnet level.
- Improves network management and security.

NSG (Network Security Group)
- Controls inbound and outbound traffic.
- Works like a firewall.
- Uses Allow and Deny rules.
- Can be attached to subnet or NIC.
- Evaluated based on priority numbers.

Route Tables (UDR)
- UDR = User Defined Route.
- Controls network traffic paths.
- Overrides Azure default routing.
- Directs traffic to firewall/NVA.
- Used for custom network designs.

Service Endpoints
- Secure connection to Azure PaaS services.
- Traffic stays on Azure backbone network.
- Extends VNET identity to Azure services.
- Supports Storage, SQL, Key Vault, etc.
- Simpler than Private Endpoint.

Private Endpoint
- Provides private IP to Azure services.
- Accesses PaaS services privately.
- Eliminates public internet exposure.
- Uses Azure Private Link.
- Improves security and compliance.

VNET Peering
- Connects two Azure VNets.
- Low latency communication.
- Uses Azure backbone network.
- No VPN Gateway required.
- Supports same or different regions.

VPN Gateway
- onnects on-premises to Azure over internet.
- Provides encrypted communication.
- Supports Site-to-Site VPN.
- Supports Point-to-Site VPN.
- Lower cost than ExpressRoute.

ExpressRoute
- Private connection to Azure.
- Does not use public internet.
- Higher security and reliability.
- Lower latency than VPN.
- Suitable for enterprise workloads.

Azure DNS
- Azure-hosted DNS service.
- Manages public and private DNS zones.
- Provides name resolution.
- Highly available and scalable.
- Integrates with Azure resources.

Application Gateway
- Layer 7 Load Balancer (HTTP/HTTPS).
- Supports URL-based routing.
- Supports SSL termination.
- Includes Web Application Firewall (WAF).
- Commonly used for web applications.

