Copilot said: Service Endpoint vs Private Endpoint
Service Endpoint

Extends VNET identity to an Azure service.
Azure service still has a public IP.
Traffic stays on the Azure backbone network.
Simpler and cheaper to configure.
Access is restricted using VNET/Subnet rules.

Private Endpoint

Creates a private IP inside your VNET.
Azure service is accessed privately.
No public internet exposure required.
Uses Azure Private Link.
More secure than Service Endpoint.

Quick Comparison
IP Address

Service Endpoint → Public IP
Private Endpoint → Private IP

Internet Exposure

Service Endpoint → Public endpoint exists
Private Endpoint → Public access can be disabled

Security

Service Endpoint → Good
Private Endpoint → Best

Access Method

Service Endpoint → Through service public endpoint
Private Endpoint → Through private IP in VNET

DNS Requirement

Service Endpoint → Usually not required
Private Endpoint → Private DNS Zone commonly required

Cost

Service Endpoint → Free
Private Endpoint → Additional cost

Interview Answer
When to use Service Endpoint?

When you need secure access from Azure VNETs to Storage Account, SQL Database, or Key Vault and public endpoint usage is acceptable.

When to use Private Endpoint?

When security and compliance require that the service be accessible only through a private IP and not exposed to the public internet.

